Burnley and Liverpool supporters this afternoon came together as one at Turf Moor in a moving demonstration of support to Clarke Carlisle.

Former Burnley, QPR and Leeds United defender Carlisle is recovering in Leeds General Infirmary after being a hit by a lorry in Yorkshire on Monday morning.

Supporters held banners and applauded at Turf Moor in the 5th minute - the shirt number Carlisle wore as a Burnley centre-half - as fans demonstrated their backing with an impeccably observed ovation for their former player.

