On Twitter, Gary Lineker said: ‘Lovely and heartfelt round of applause in the 5th minute at Turf Moor for Clarke Carlisle. Wish him well.’

The former PFA Chairman remains in a serious condition in hospital but his wife Gemma assured that he was recuperating well on Tuesday afternoon.

‘Clarke’s very poorly but he’s alive and stable. Best Christmas gift we as a family could wish for. Thanks again.’ she Tweeted on Christmas Eve.

The incident took place near Bishopthorpe at 7.30am on Monday, with the road closed to allow the air ambulance to arrive at the scene. Police are appealing for witnesses.

